      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Former Kiwi RAKERO ROCKET NZ (4) has made a big impact since joining Jason Grimson and been dominant in winning his last two starts over this distance at Menangle. Hasn't raced for five weeks but was kept up to the mark with a trial and has the speed to push forward from this draw. The one to beat. In-form Queenslander CHEERSTOLOU (3) draws inside Rakero Rocket and has enough pace to make things interesting early. This is a step up in class but he has been a revelation since joining Donny Smith for this campaign, winning nine of his 10 Albion Park starts over 1660m including his last six on the trot. BULLETPROOF BOY (10) has copped the visitor's draw but has been very good against the big guns in Victoria so far this season including a Bendigo Cup victory over Kingman and he downed champion pacer Leap To Fame in a Smoken Up Sprint win at Melton last year. Respect. HELLUVA NZ (1) has been coming from wider or second line barriers so the ace draw should see him competitive.",
